      <Description>Plasma structures at 400-850km altitudes in the equatorial ionosphere have been measured by the C/NOFS Planar Langmuir Probe (PLP). This PLP data set contains 1-sec resolution ion number density and its standard deviation, electron density, electron temperature, spacecraft potential, and spacecraft position in geodetic coordinates. As of 5/13/2010, the data were preliminary.</Description>
